      About this item

      • App Control(NO REMOTE): Download the free AiDot app and pair the BR30 wifi light bulbs with your WiFi (only supports 2.4G, not support 5.0Ghz). As long as the smart bulbs stay connected to WiFi, you can easily control their on/off, brightness (1%~100%), color, etc. with your phone. NOTE: NOT WORK WITH ANY KINDS OF WALL DIMMERS
      • CRI >90 & 2700K Warm White: The BR30 color lights bulbs illuminate no fliker 2700k warm white light, CRI > 90 can effectively restore the true color of the object, comfortable your eyes.
      • Customize Schedules & Scenes: Set different schedule times to turn on/off the flood light bulbs according to your daily routines. Various preset features like Bonfire, Party, Sleeping, Reading, etc. and scenes are available to meet your demand.
      • Voice Control (NO HUB REQUIRED): Seamless integration with Google home and Alexa. You can control these Linkind led colour changing light bulbs with voice commands. No hub required.

      Product Description

      How to connect the bulbs to AiDot APP?

      1. Turn on the bulb, open AiDot APP, tap"Add Device", select "Nearby"to connect via Bluetooth.
      2. Follow the prompts to turn on location and Bluetooth permissions.
      3. After automatic detection by the app, select the detected bulb.
      4. Select home network, enter its password and wait to connect.

      What to do if the bulb offline?

      1. Step 1: Power on the bulbs.
      2. Step 2: Turn on and off the light for six times in a row, the interval is about 1.5s, not too fast or too slow.
      3. Step 3: Turn it on at the 7th time, bulbs will run a color shift, which means the resetting is done and it is in pairing mood. After resetting, please re-add the bulb to AiDot APP.

      Linkind Br30 Smart Wifi Light Bulbs

      How to Connect Alexa

      1. First sign in both the AiDot APP and Alexa APP. Next tap "Aidotor" in the AiDot APP, select "Integration".
      2. Follow the on-screen instructions to link with Alexa.

      • Wattage: 8W equivalent 60W
      • Brightness: 650lm
      • Color Temp: 1800K-6500K
      • Dimmable via App: 1%~100%
      • Lifespan: 25000+
      • Do not install the smart bulb on a circuit with a dimmer switch.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5 out of 5 stars
      For those confused about matter vs non-matter
      I'm new to smart bulbs and didn't realize the difference between this product and the identical one that says "matter". I ended up ordering both and hopefully can help someone else wondering the same thing.Both products are stamped with this model on the bulb stem: LS0101911266, they had different date codes (2409 and 2410).However, in the app:The product without "matter" reports:- Hardware version: A001419- Firmware: 2.01.35The product with "matter" reports:- Hardware version: A001498- Firmware: 3.09.13Both reported that their firmware was up to date, so I went with the "matter" version as it appears to be a newer hardware/firmware and both are the same price.
